  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare bill of quantities for tendering of subcontract packages including sourcing out of subcontractors/suppliers</li>\n  <li>Handle contract negotiations with subcontractors/suppliers and prepare subcontract agreement</li>\n  <li>Handle cost monitoring, adherence to contract specifications and drawings</li>\n  <li>Prepare payment certificates of subcontractor</li>\n  <li>Evaluate and negotiate revisions, changes and additions to contractual agreement with subcontractors</li>\n  <li>Prepare variation orders and reconcile with the client’s quantity surveyors in accordance to the contract agreement</li>\n  <li>Prepare monthly progress claim to client and assist in preparation of cashflow forecast for submission to client</li>\n  <li>Coordinate changes in plans with design team and review the potential variation claims to client</li>\n  <li>Provide assistance with either the tender process or project execution</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / Degree in Quantity Surveying/ Civil Engineering or other related field</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of local working experience in Civil and Building projects</li>\n  <li>A good team player with good initiative and positive work attitude</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently with minimum supervision</li>\n</ul>",
